diff --git a/docs/property-filters.md b/docs/property-filters.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..8e7d742
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/property-filters.md
@@ -0,0 +1,76 @@
+# Property Filters
+
+The property filter extends the city search with optional criteria while
+keeping the main search bar compact.
+
+## Available Filters
+
+- City
+- Property type
+- Minimum and maximum warm rent
+- Minimum living space
+- Minimum number of rooms
+- Pets allowed or not allowed
+- Minimum internet speed
+- Available by date
+
+## How It Works
+
+The filter implementation is split across two files:
+
+- `app/components/search.tsx` renders the controls and creates the URL query.
+- `app/src/routes/Exposes.tsx` reads the query and filters the property data.
+
+The additional controls are hidden behind the `Filters` button. A badge shows
+how many optional filters are active.
+
+When the form is submitted, active values are stored as URL parameters:
+
+```text
+/exposes?q=Hamburg&type=House&maxRent=3000&minRooms=4&pets=yes
+```
+
+This makes filtered result pages shareable and reload-safe.
+
+## URL Parameters
+
+| Parameter | Example | Meaning |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `q` | `Hamburg` | Selected city |
+| `type` | `House` | Exact property type |
+| `minRent` | `1000` | Minimum monthly warm rent |
+| `maxRent` | `2500` | Maximum monthly warm rent |
+| `minSize` | `80` | Minimum living space in m² |
+| `minRooms` | `3` | Minimum number of rooms |
+| `pets` | `yes` | `yes` for allowed, `no` for not allowed |
+| `minInternet` | `500` | Minimum speed in Mbit/s |
+| `availableBy` | `2026-08-01` | Property must be available by this date |
+
+Empty or invalid numeric values use an unrestricted default. The city value is
+validated against the cities generated from `app/data/exposes.json`.
+
+## Filter Logic
+
+A property must satisfy every active filter:
+
+- Range filters use inclusive comparisons.
+- City and property type use exact matches.
+- Room and size filters define minimum values.
+- The availability date includes properties available on or before that date.
+- No URL parameter means that criterion is ignored.
+
+If no properties match, the results page displays an empty state.
+
+## Clearing Filters
+
+`Clear filters` resets all optional filters but keeps the selected city. The
+new state is applied after submitting the search again.
+
+## Extending the Filter
+
+To add another filter:
+
+1. Add its state and control in `app/components/search.tsx`.
+2. Include it in the `filters` object so it becomes a URL parameter.
+3. Read and apply the parameter in `app/src/routes/Exposes.tsx`.
+4. Keep the parameter optional so existing URLs continue to work.
\ No newline at end of file
